claim.claim-text:
1. A portable computer operating at a variable speed, and having a computer case, the computer comprising: 
means for detecting coupling to an external docking station; 
a set of mating openings; 
a set of air intake openings; 
a processor located proximate the sets of openings; and 
means for varying the speed of the computer based on detected coupling of the computer to the external docking station.

16. The method of claim 15 and further comprising the steps of; 
monitoring the temperature inside the portable computer; and 
slowing down the processor if the temperature reaches a predetermined value.

19. A computer system comprising: 
a portable computer; 
a docking station; 
an opening in a case of the portable computer located to mate with a corresponding mating opening in the external docking station; 
an air intake opening in the case of the portable computer; 
a processor having a heat sink positioned between the openings; and 
a fan mounted within the docking station for moving air through the mating openings to cool the processor in the portable computer.

29. A computer system comprising: 
a portable computer; 
a docking station; 
a processor in the portable computer; 
a first heat pipe positioned thermally proximate the processor; 
a second heat pipe positioned within the docking station to mate with the first heat pipe when the portable computer and docking station are mated; and 
a fan mounted within the docking station for moving air past the second heat pipe to actively cool the portable computer.

30. An information handling system comprising: 
a portable computer; 
a docking station; 
a sensor configured to detect coupling of the portable computer to the docking station; 
said portable computer including a processor configured to operate at a low processing speed; and 
wherein the processor is further configured to operate at a high processing speed when the sensor detects that the portable computer is coupled to the docking station. portable computer operating at a variable speed, and having a computer case, the computer comprising: 
means for detecting coupling to an external docking station; 
a set of mating openings; 
a set of air intake openings; 
a processor located proximate the sets of openings; and 
means for varying the speed of the computer based on detected coupling of the computer to the external docking station.

35. A portable computer operating at a variable speed, and having a computer case, the computer comprising: 
means for detecting coupling to an external docking station; 
a set of mating openings; 
a set of air intake openings; 
a processor located proximate to the sets of openings and positioned in an airflow created between the set of mating openings and the set of air intake openings; and 
means for varying the speed of the computer based on detected coupling of the computer to the external docking station.

50. A computer system comprising: 
a portable computer; 
a docking station; 
a processor in the portable computer; 
a first heat pipe positioned thermally proximate to the processor; 
a second heat pipe positioned within the docking station to mate with the first heat pipe when the portable computer and docking station are mated; and 
a fan mounted within the docking station for moving air past the second heat pipe to actively cool the portable computer.

53. An information handling system having a portable computer operating at a variable speed, and having a computer case, the computer comprising: 
means for detecting coupling to an external docking station; 
a set of mating openings; 
a set of air intake openings; 
a processor located proximate to the sets of openings and positioned in an airflow created between the set of mating openings and the set of air intake openings; and 
means for varying the speed of the computer based on detected coupling of the computer to the external docking station.
